First, we need to find the symmetric difference of A and B (A △ B). The symmetric difference of two sets is the set of elements which are in either of the sets but not in their intersection.

A = {1, 5, 7}
B = {1, 2, 3}
Intersection of A and B = {1}

Now, we find the elements that are in either A or B but not in their intersection:

A △ B = {2, 3, 5, 7}

Next, we find the symmetric difference of (A △ B) and C:

(A △ B) = {2, 3, 5, 7}
C = {2, 3, 7, 8}
Intersection of (A △ B) and C = {2, 3, 7}

Now, we find the elements that are in either (A △ B) or C but not in their intersection:

(A △ B) △ C = {5, 8}

So, the symmetric difference (A △ B) △ C is {5, 8}.
